--- @target: std.fs.path
Path manipulation utilities for constructing, parsing, and normalizing filesystem paths.
---

--- @target: join
Joins two path segments with a forward slash separator.

@param base The base path segment.
@param child The child path segment to append.
@return The joined path string.
---

--- @target: normalize
Normalizes a path by resolving dot segments and standardizing separators.

@param value The path to normalize.
@return The normalized path string.
---

--- @target: is_absolute
Checks whether a path is absolute (starts from root).

@param value The path to check.
@return True if the path is absolute.
---

--- @target: is_relative
Checks whether a path is relative (does not start from root).

@param value The path to check.
@return True if the path is relative.
---

--- @target: absolute
Converts a relative path to an absolute path relative to a given base directory.

@param value The relative path.
@param base The base directory to resolve against.
@return The absolute path string.
---

--- @target: relative
Computes the relative path from a base directory to a target path.

@param value The target path.
@param from The base directory.
@return The relative path string.
---

--- @target: base
Extracts the filename (last segment) from a path.

@param value The full path.
@return The filename part without directory.
---

--- @target: dir
Extracts the directory part of a path (everything before the last slash).

@param value The full path.
@return The directory part.
---

--- @target: ext
Extracts the file extension (the part after the last dot in the filename).

@param value The path to extract extension from.
@return The extension without the leading dot, or empty string if none.
---

--- @target: name_without_extension
Extracts the filename without its extension.

@param value The full path.
@return The filename without the extension part.
---

--- @target: has_ext
Checks whether a path has a specific file extension.

@param value The path to check.
@param expected_ext The extension to check for (with or without leading dot).
@return True if the path has the expected extension.
---

--- @target: change_ext
Replaces or removes the extension of a filename in a path.

@param value The full path.
@param new_ext The new extension to set (with or without leading dot). Empty string removes extension.
@return The path with the extension changed.
---
